# REST API Testing - JWT Auth Server
# Use with REST Client VS Code extension or Postman

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000/api/auth
@accessToken = 
@refreshToken = 

### Health Check
GET http://localhost:5000/health

### 1. Register a new user
POST @baseUrl/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "testuser@example.com",
  "password": "TestPassword123!",
  "name": "Test User"
}

### 2. Login
POST @baseUrl/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "testuser@example.com",
  "password": "TestPassword123!"
}

### 3. Get current user (requires valid access token)
GET @baseUrl/me
Authorization: Bearer @accessToken

### 4. Refresh access token
POST @baseUrl/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "@refreshToken"
}

### 5. Logout (revoke refresh token)
POST @baseUrl/logout
Authorization: Bearer @accessToken
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "@refreshToken"
}

### 6. Admin endpoint (requires ADMIN role)
GET http://localhost:5000/api/auth/admin/users
Authorization: Bearer @accessToken
